Package: mixology
Title: Sentiment Analysis Lexicons and Tools for Covid-19 Crisis Communication
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Laurence", "Dierickx", email = "hello@ohmybox.info", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides eight sentiment lexicons for comparative opinion mining,
    including two manually annotated lexicons developed for the Mixology research
    project (Covid-19 crisis, Western Europe, December 2021) and six harmonised
    general-purpose English sentiment dictionaries: General Inquirer, MPQA
    Subjectivity Lexicon, Bing Liu, NRC Emotion Lexicon, AFINN, and
    Loughran-McDonald. All lexicons share a common three-category polarity scheme
    (positive, negative, ambiguous). Also includes a custom stop words list and
    negation markers. Provides functions for tokenisation, negation-aware scoring,
    and weighted comparative sentiment analysis.
